Of course I go on tilt. Why do u think I have all these systems, track all this
data, & have all these risk management rules, even though they suck the
excitement and fun out of trading?  it is to protect me from MYSELF. The human
brain is NOT wired for trading. period.

The brain wants to take profits quickly & let losers run. Which is the EXACT
opposite of profitable trading. Thats why ppl bank over & over again, but
eventually give it all back. Then 2yrs later they realize they have a 70-90%
winrate yet are barely at breakeven, if not negative

U'll never break free frm that cycle until u realize that ur brain is the enemy.
And the ONLY way to counter ur primal impulses is to systematize ur trading.
SPECIFIC entry rules, SPECIFIC exit rules, SPECIFIC stock selection rules. none
of that freestyling shit.
 -- AllDayFaders, via Twitter



