Across all market conditions, trading styles, time frames & traders, one rule
holds true: 5-10% of all trades account for 90% of profits. Awareness of the
90/10 rule provides you with an opportunity to focus on those trades that, if
they work, will produce material profits, while if they don't, won't cripple
you from a capital-preservation perspective.
 -- Ken Grant, risk manager for Paul Tudor Jones


