We always look for cyclicality, some sort of two-sided action. We never trade
expecting the market to move in one direction only;  if you do that throughout
your career, you're destined to be a huge loser. If you play the market to move
outside the normal distribution curve, you're going to lose for your entire
career - this is why most investors lose. The market doesn't do that. It doesn't
accommodate your directional ideas or thoughts; it always stays in a range.
That's the nature of any marketplace.
 -- Tom Sosnoff


