UBI is just another word for centralised state socialism because it cannot
be implemented without state controls on production and on prices. The
theory falls apart completely without state controls on the market because
the extra income, which has no real value underlying it, simply gets
swallowed up by inflation. If it is universal then it is worthless because
the value of a currency lies in its relativity to the amount of it floating
about. You are also going to need strict border controls to prevent capital
flight because those who do have a lot of money are not going to share it
voluntarily; except this time that capital flight will be more severe given
that it is so easy now to transfer wealth electronically. 
 -- Svetlana Voreskova, on Medium 


