Oxygen respiration is the most efficient form of respiration in existence
in biology. Molecular oxygen is the electron acceptor, and it happens to be
one with the lowest energy level of acceptance and the greatest electron
affinity in existence in the universe, and definitely the best in these two
aspects of all the commonly available substances in the universe that life
can easily get access to.
 -- Adam Wu, on Quora 


Evolution acts on a species ability to leave offspring. It doesn't care
about immortality. YOU do, but evolution doesn't care. It isn't
teleological. It doesn't "try" to make things a certain way. Evolution is a
blind force that acts on fertility. Evolution is simply this: every
creature is different than its parents. Some of those differences result in
one offspring being able to leave more offspring than its siblings or
peers. Over time, those small differences accumulate.
 -- Dan Holiday, on Quora 


Failure is an investment with compound interest.
