to come short and short again, because there is no effort without error and
shortcoming. It is the man who actually strives to do the great deeds, who
knows the great enthusiasm and knows the great devotion, who spends himself
on a worthy cause, who, at best, knows in the end the triumph of great
achievement. And who, at worst, if he fails, at least fails while daring
