The default position in any debate is whatever both parties in the debate
can agree on. The more improbable the hypothesis, the greater the need for
justification. The common ground will be everything that appears to the
debaters to be true, such as the existence of the physical universe. It is
the theist who wants to go beyond it and posit the existence of a
transcendent being that stands in greater need of justification. Atheism
doesn't require defense because it is up to theists bear the burden of
proof of something implausible. 


