If you are a really diligent worker who charges by the hour, you have
100,000 hours to sell in your lifetime, give or take. What can you average
per hour over your lifetime? That's your earning capacity. But what if you
have three or eight or eighty-eight employees working for you? Now it's
quite a bit more open-ended, yes? And for every working hour you have, you
will have about six times that number as your total life. Money...
equity... can be earning 24/7/52. It can be earning even while you're
sleeping or on vacation or working. If you can average a dollar of interest
an hour, that's the same as an extra $6 an hour in wages. If you want to
earn wealth as a capitalist, you have to build a grubstake and put it at
risk.
 -- Charles Tips 


