Ignoring house loads, the ratio of drive distance (at 4kts) to regen
distance (at 5kts) is about 1 to 40. Motor one mile at 4kts (15 minutes)
and you need to sail 40 miles at 5kts (8 hours) to get the charge back.
If you use a radio, autopilot or lights, the ratio gets worse.
 -- Eric <ewdysar@yahoo.com> in the 'electricboats' Yahoo group


An easy question is "how much gas do you usually use in a single day on the
water?" Just thinking about the batteries, if you use golf cart style
batteries, the usable equivalent of a 1 gallon gas tank will weigh about
800 pounds and cost about $2000. Upgrading to AGM will drop the weight to
about 750 pounds and cost about $4000. Going high tech, you could buy
Lithium cells that only weigh 350 pounds and cost about $6200. All of that
for a "gas tank" that will drive your boat as far as 1 gallon of gas today.
 -- Eric <ewdysar@yahoo.com> in the 'electricboats' Yahoo group


