opposition, are not necessarily contradictory. The human body is
supplied with muscles so arranged that one set can oppose and frustrate
the action of another set. Nevertheless, although there is a wrong way
to use them, the body still has to have both sets to function properly.
Bear this in mind. A quality may be indispensable, but insufficient by
itself. And the necessary additional quality may be its apparent
opposite.
