In an open system, a competitive advantage doesn't derive from locking
in customers, but rather from understanding the fast-moving system
better than anyone else and using that knowledge to generate better,
more innovative products. The successful company in an open system is
both a fast innovator and a thought leader; the brand value of thought
leadership attracts customers and then fast innovation keeps them. This
isn't easy - far from it - but fast companies have nothing to fear,
and when they are successful they can generate great shareholder value.
 -- Jonathan Rosenberg, Senior VP, Google


