The next thing I've learned from my failures is something familiar to
the test-driven development crowd. It's mandatory to fail early. You
need to know you're in trouble right away. That's essential when taking
over an existing project or starting something new. You have to find out
how you're doing within weeks. Not quarters, not months. The longer you
wait, the more inertia the failure will have.
 -- Reginald Braithwaite


