energy. And you gotta notice it when you do it. Here's the trick: Those
things that you feel most terrified about releasing, that seem to
contain your entire identity and without which you wouldn't fully
recognize yourself, well, maybe they should be the first things to feel
the razor: jobs, cars, hair, photographs, bedsheets, houses, ideologies,
religions. To what do you cling? What holds all your fear of change?

