I honestly don't care if you or anyone else gets "converted" to Linux. I
don't have to. I'm no better off if you do; I'm no worse off if you don't.

What I do care about is making useful information and help available
to people using Linux or interested in it. Why? Partly to redeem the trust
shown by others when they helped me. Partly because it's interesting.
Partly because researching and then teaching things I usually start knowing
little about is the best way I know to learn. And partly out of pure,
unadulterated self-interest: people knowing your name is at least a foot in
the door, in the IT business.
 -- Rick Moen


