it's like to be bored. The ocean fills some nameless void within me;
without it, I feel myself starving to death in the midst of plenty. I've
never been a religious man, all that I have read about religions
describes straitjackets which I could only wear by contorting myself
into unnatural shapes - but I've found something in Ocean that fills
that niche in me. It's not written in any books I know of, except for
shadows of it in my log, but it has to do with great admiration, love,
and respect for the infinite power and majesty of it, and with the joy
of knowing that I can live and prosper there if I only follow the old
rules etched in the stones of the fjords by the storms over millions of
years. It takes knowledge, effort - sometimes effort far beyond what
those living on land would consider possible - scrupulous honesty, and
unrelenting attention to duty, but it pays back in self-respect,
