A quick check is reboot your Solaris system with "set kmem_flags = 0xf" in
/etc/system; this enables the kernel memory debugger and causes all
uninitialized data reads to 0xbaddcafe; if it reads from previously
free memory you'll find 0xdeadbeef; if you read from a buffer's readzone
you'll get 0xfeedface. A packet returning bad data would most likely
contain 0xbaddcafe. 
 -- Casper, in Bugtraq


