ethics transcends legality: the idea that an action can be legal
but unethical. If "they paid for it" means that all legal acts
are ethical, then you've pretty much defined away the whole idea
of professional ethics. *That* is probably best not attempted on
comp.security.misc/unix.
 -- From the comp.security.misc/unix FAQ


